Subtitle downloaded with
Sublight (www.sublight.me)

2
00:02:20,760 --> 00:02:22,955
Une biere, s'il vous plaît.

3
00:02:41,680 --> 00:02:43,398
Merci.

4
00:04:23,560 --> 00:04:24,993
<i>We are closed.</i>

5
00:04:25,080 --> 00:04:26,752
<i>Just a small drink.</i>

6
00:04:33,200 --> 00:04:35,156
<i>The toilets?</i>

7
00:05:25,920 --> 00:05:29,515
<i>A quick drink and then I'll leave.</i>

8
00:05:32,400 --> 00:05:34,231
Why are you rushing off?

9
00:05:34,360 --> 00:05:37,397
- Hmm?
- I said, why are you rushing off?

10
00:05:37,480 --> 00:05:39,118
<i>I don't understand.</i>

11
00:05:40,400 --> 00:05:42,231
The man from Bristol called ya.

12
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:50,268
- What man?
- The man in the wheelchair.

13
00:06:25,440 --> 00:06:27,749
What were you doing back here?

14
00:06:29,280 --> 00:06:30,633
Lady,

15
00:06:30,720 --> 00:06:34,156
I never walk into a place
I don't know how to walk out of.

16
00:06:35,320 --> 00:06:37,151
Then why would you get into that van?

17
00:06:37,240 --> 00:06:39,549
You know the reason.

18
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:49,794
Make yourselves at home.

19
00:07:49,880 --> 00:07:52,314
You've come a long way.

20
00:07:52,400 --> 00:07:55,278
- Thanks for coming.
- What's the job?

21
00:07:55,400 --> 00:07:58,995
There's some people
who have something we require.

22
00:07:59,120 --> 00:08:02,396
- And we want you to get it from them.
- It involves shooting?

23
00:08:03,480 --> 00:08:05,948
You must be tired.

24
00:08:06,040 --> 00:08:08,156
We'll tell you more tomorrow.

25
00:08:14,520 --> 00:08:18,513
Seven fat years
and seven lean years.

26
00:08:18,600 --> 00:08:21,319
- That's what it says in the Bible.
- You ever kill anybody?

27
00:08:21,400 --> 00:08:23,868
I hurt somebody's feelings once.

28
00:08:30,160 --> 00:08:31,832
Don't I know you?

29
00:08:33,760 --> 00:08:37,150
I don't think so. I'd remember.

30
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:45,797
Okay, two-hour shifts.

31
00:08:45,920 --> 00:08:48,514
I'll watch the front,
you guys watch the back.

32
00:08:50,680 --> 00:08:52,193
Merci.

33
00:09:04,520 --> 00:09:06,317
You awake, then?

34
00:09:08,080 --> 00:09:10,548
Hmm?

35
00:09:12,960 --> 00:09:14,757
How we doin'?

36
00:09:19,360 --> 00:09:20,713
Yep.

37
00:09:38,200 --> 00:09:40,031
You labour or management?

38
00:09:40,240 --> 00:09:44,119
If I was management,
I wouldn't have given you a cigarette.

39
00:09:45,760 --> 00:09:49,639
I am the tour guide.
Over there is the Eiffel Tower.

40
00:09:49,720 --> 00:09:52,359
Over here, the Louvre.
Over there, les toilettes.

41
00:09:52,480 --> 00:09:54,710
What do I call you?

42
00:09:54,840 --> 00:09:57,434
- My name is Vincent.
- Sam.

43
00:10:00,520 --> 00:10:05,036
As per the agreement,
your salary will be $5,000 a week

44
00:10:05,120 --> 00:10:07,680
with a minimum
of four weeks' work.

45
00:10:07,800 --> 00:10:10,109
On the successful completion
of the mission,

46
00:10:10,240 --> 00:10:13,915
you will each receive
a bonus of $20,000.

47
00:10:15,320 --> 00:10:19,233
And by the way,
my name is Deirdre.

48
00:10:19,320 --> 00:10:22,153
- The broad outlines of the mission are...
- Who are your principals?

49
00:10:22,280 --> 00:10:24,032
For you,
there's no one but myself.

50
00:10:24,240 --> 00:10:26,071
Huh?

51
00:10:26,160 --> 00:10:29,038
And what can we infer
from your charming Irish lilt?

52
00:10:29,160 --> 00:10:32,118
- Anything you like.
- Where's the equipment?

53
00:10:32,240 --> 00:10:34,674
Tell me what you need, make a list,
and give it to Vincent.

54
00:10:34,760 --> 00:10:37,877
- Some of the equipment's quite technical.
- If it's in Paris, I'll find it.

55
00:10:37,960 --> 00:10:41,316
This is what we're after.

56
00:10:41,440 --> 00:10:45,228
We need to take it intact from several
men who'll be intent on preventing us.

57
00:10:45,360 --> 00:10:47,510
- How many men?
- You American?

58
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:51,309
I think the group will be between
five and eight. No more than eight.

59
00:10:51,440 --> 00:10:55,797
- You don't know for sure?
- Not now but I will know before the event.

60
00:10:55,880 --> 00:10:59,270
If you don't know,
why say between five and eight?

61
00:10:59,360 --> 00:11:01,191
There's two to three cars.
The group's travellin'.

62
00:11:01,280 --> 00:11:02,599
- They're not in Paris?
- No.

63
00:11:02,680 --> 00:11:03,556
Where are they?

64
00:11:03,680 --> 00:11:06,148
- You'll find out soon enough.
- What's in the case?

65
00:11:07,800 --> 00:11:10,633
Our plan, in broad strokes, is an ambush.

66
00:11:10,760 --> 00:11:13,194
It's to hit the car,
to take them in transit.

67
00:11:13,320 --> 00:11:16,915
- Transit? City? Country?
- Right now, as I said, I don't know.

68
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:19,309
But we've to move very quickly.

69
00:11:19,400 --> 00:11:23,678
We'll start with this: Ambush
and assault on two to three vehicles,

70
00:11:23,760 --> 00:11:28,276
five to eight men, and our objective
is the safe retrieval of this case.

71
00:11:28,360 --> 00:11:31,909
Tell Vincent
what it is you'll need.

72
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:36,676
What do we know about them?
Are they French? Who are they?

73
00:11:36,760 --> 00:11:39,957
All you need to know right now
is that they're very unpleasant.

74
00:11:40,080 --> 00:11:44,471
- You've done this kind of thing before?
- You know...

75
00:11:44,560 --> 00:11:45,629
How difficult can it be?

76
00:11:45,720 --> 00:11:47,756
We have no idea
how these men will be armed?

77
00:11:47,880 --> 00:11:50,189
It seems they'll be
very well armed, indeed.

78
00:11:50,320 --> 00:11:52,276
Where are we going and
how are we getting back from there?

79
00:11:52,360 --> 00:11:55,397
It'll be in France, and the group
will disband at the RV point.

80
00:11:55,480 --> 00:11:58,995
<i>- What does she mean?</i>
<i>- After that, we're on our own.</i>

81
00:11:59,080 --> 00:12:01,674
<i>- It's a military term.</i>
<i>- That's right.</i>

82
00:12:01,760 --> 00:12:03,273
Larry, tell Vincent what you'll need.

83
00:12:03,360 --> 00:12:08,070
Something very fast. Audi S-8.
Something that can shove.

84
00:12:08,160 --> 00:12:10,799
I'm going to have it for you
by the afternoon.

85
00:12:10,920 --> 00:12:14,435
I'll also need a nitrous system.
I've got the specs.

86
00:12:18,920 --> 00:12:21,229
What do you use, weapons-wise?

87
00:12:21,360 --> 00:12:23,476
- Hmm?
- Weapons.

88
00:12:23,560 --> 00:12:26,518
- I'm a... I'm a weapons man.
- Weapons man.

89
00:12:26,600 --> 00:12:28,431
- Yeah.
- Okay.

90
00:12:28,560 --> 00:12:32,394
They tend to settle the argument.
So what do you favour?

91
00:12:32,520 --> 00:12:35,956
Well, you know. It's a toolbox.
You put the tools in for the job.

92
00:12:36,080 --> 00:12:37,195
What?

93
00:12:37,280 --> 00:12:40,272
You know,
I actually favour the old 1911.

94
00:12:40,360 --> 00:12:43,636
.45. Old gun.

95
00:12:45,400 --> 00:12:47,436
It served my country well.
A long time.

96
00:12:47,560 --> 00:12:49,835
Your country!

97
00:12:49,960 --> 00:12:51,916
Not done too well, have you,
last few wars?

98
00:12:52,040 --> 00:12:54,349
Perhaps not, but at least
we don't go around whining about it.

99
00:12:56,880 --> 00:12:57,630
You ex-military?

100
00:12:57,720 --> 00:12:59,631
No, I got my job
through the New York Times.

101
00:13:01,160 --> 00:13:04,311
<i>- Don't let him get you down.</i>
- It don't mean nothin' to me.

102
00:13:04,400 --> 00:13:06,152
<i>I say what I think.</i>

103
00:13:06,240 --> 00:13:08,595
Are you ex-military?

104
00:13:08,720 --> 00:13:10,836
Boys at Hereford?

105
00:13:10,960 --> 00:13:13,520
I'm sorry, but I'd like to go backwards.
The line of retreat is...

106
00:13:13,600 --> 00:13:17,957
She just told you.
We meet back at the RV, disband.

107
00:13:18,080 --> 00:13:21,868
I understand. I'm just trying to get
a vague notion of the opposition.

108
00:13:21,960 --> 00:13:27,432
We're gonna cause some animosity.
How many will be coming after us?

109
00:13:27,560 --> 00:13:30,472
- You worried about your own skin?
- Yeah, I am.

110
00:13:30,560 --> 00:13:32,391
It covers my body.

111
00:13:33,760 --> 00:13:36,991
All your concerns will be addressed
before we leave.

112
00:13:37,120 --> 00:13:39,509
- Electronics and commo.
- Not more than three cars?

113
00:13:39,600 --> 00:13:40,953
That is our information.

114
00:13:41,160 --> 00:13:43,674
- Can you get me a simulator?
- What's a simulator?

115
00:13:43,760 --> 00:13:46,877
Gunpowder. Sound only, no lead.
Sounds like a pistol.

116
00:13:46,960 --> 00:13:48,473
Quite diverting.

117
00:13:48,560 --> 00:13:52,075
Listen, I'm also gonna need
some bigger injection jets.

118
00:13:52,160 --> 00:13:54,720
The Bosch is not gonna do it.
They have to be custom-made.

119
00:13:54,800 --> 00:13:57,678
We going north? We going south?

120
00:13:57,760 --> 00:14:00,877
I'd like some new clothes.

121
00:14:00,960 --> 00:14:03,520
- Vincent will sort you out.
- I'll take care of it.

122
00:14:10,120 --> 00:14:13,157
- So what brought you here?
- A fella that doesn't work so well.

123
00:14:14,440 --> 00:14:16,715
The man in the wheelchair?

124
00:14:17,560 --> 00:14:18,993
How did he get there?

125
00:14:19,080 --> 00:14:23,710
That was in your neck of the woods,
back in the late unpleasantness.

126
00:14:34,600 --> 00:14:35,874
Good reflexes.

127
00:14:37,320 --> 00:14:39,038
Oh, yeah.

128
00:14:39,520 --> 00:14:41,636
They die hard.

129
00:14:48,280 --> 00:14:51,750
- Interrogation.
- What?

130
00:14:51,840 --> 00:14:55,753
- Methods to withstand interrogation.
- You've done that?

131
00:14:55,880 --> 00:14:58,713
We were taught
to hold out indefinitely.

132
00:15:00,440 --> 00:15:04,035
- Nobody can hold out indefinitely.
- Ah, is that so?

133
00:15:04,120 --> 00:15:09,513
Everybody has a limit. I spent
some time in interrogation... once.

134
00:15:09,600 --> 00:15:11,875
- They make it hard on you?
- They don't make it easy.

135
00:15:12,200 --> 00:15:16,113
Yeah, it was unpleasant.
I held out as long as I could.

136
00:15:16,200 --> 00:15:18,794
All the stuff they tried.

137
00:15:18,880 --> 00:15:21,110
You just can't hold out for ever.

138
00:15:21,200 --> 00:15:23,794
- Impossible.
- How'd they finally get to you?

139
00:15:23,920 --> 00:15:26,559
- They gave me a grasshopper.
- What's a grasshopper?

140
00:15:26,680 --> 00:15:30,992
That's two part gin, two part brandy,
one part creme de menthe...

141
00:15:31,120 --> 00:15:33,076
Fuckin' smartass!

142
00:15:33,920 --> 00:15:36,798
- Can you find this place?
- Of course.

143
00:15:36,920 --> 00:15:38,751
I know it.

144
00:15:38,880 --> 00:15:41,758
That's where
they wanna do the exchange.

145
00:15:41,880 --> 00:15:43,632
You're gonna exchange for cash?

146
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:48,559
- You know these people?
- My people know them.

147
00:15:48,680 --> 00:15:50,830
Your people have done business
with them before?

148
00:15:50,920 --> 00:15:53,639
Or these people
just gave your people a number?

149
00:16:03,960 --> 00:16:06,155
Larry.

150
00:16:09,680 --> 00:16:13,195
Okay. If we're gonna do it,
let's do the goddamn thing right.

151
00:16:15,960 --> 00:16:18,633
- Hey!
- I'm busy.

152
00:16:19,840 --> 00:16:22,070
Okay, come on. Let's go.

153
00:16:22,200 --> 00:16:25,556
The answers to your questions
I'll know when I get back.

154
00:16:25,640 --> 00:16:28,632
- I'll go with you.
- Go with them.

155
00:16:48,080 --> 00:16:49,877
Who does this girl work for?

156
00:16:49,960 --> 00:16:54,158
Well, she works for our betters.

157
00:16:54,240 --> 00:16:57,312
It seems that's what
we're meant to know.

158
00:17:04,760 --> 00:17:07,638
Always a waiting game.

159
00:17:07,720 --> 00:17:11,395
- What?
- It's a waiting game.

160
00:17:13,800 --> 00:17:16,951
Hey, wait.
Would you not do that, please?

161
00:17:18,960 --> 00:17:21,918
Bad for the night vision, yeah?

162
00:17:27,840 --> 00:17:30,035
There they are.

163
00:18:16,360 --> 00:18:18,954
- You have the list?
- Yes, I have it.

164
00:18:19,080 --> 00:18:20,718
Give it to me.

165
00:18:23,880 --> 00:18:26,314
Money?

166
00:18:27,520 --> 00:18:29,954
Okay. You follow my lead.

167
00:18:30,080 --> 00:18:32,230
Just make sure you watch my back.

168
00:18:36,800 --> 00:18:38,438
<i>Don't make any sudden moves.</i>

169
00:18:38,880 --> 00:18:42,316
<i>Just because we're buying guns</i>
<i>doesn't mean we didn't bring any.</i>

170
00:18:42,400 --> 00:18:45,551
<i>Don't worry. Everything's fine.</i>

171
00:18:48,080 --> 00:18:50,594
You want to back him up?

172
00:18:54,400 --> 00:18:56,436
What would I profit from your death?

173
00:18:56,520 --> 00:18:59,830
- Well, you'd have the money.
- I have the money already.

174
00:19:01,680 --> 00:19:04,035
I'll watch the back.

175
00:19:07,960 --> 00:19:09,518
<i>- Have you got it all?</i>
- Oui.

176
00:19:11,280 --> 00:19:14,511
<i>- You're sure?</i>
<i>- Of course. Come and see.</i>

177
00:19:24,400 --> 00:19:25,355
<i>There it is!</i>

178
00:19:44,520 --> 00:19:46,875
It's not all here.

179
00:19:48,720 --> 00:19:50,870
- Vincent.
- What?

180
00:19:54,680 --> 00:19:57,274
It's not all here.

181
00:19:57,360 --> 00:19:59,112
- C'est tout?
- Ah, non, non, non.

182
00:19:59,280 --> 00:20:03,353
Le patron va contrôler I'argent.
Vous aurez le reste de la marchandise.

183
00:20:03,440 --> 00:20:07,319
Tiens. Il est la dans la voiture,
avec le patron.

184
00:20:07,400 --> 00:20:11,678
He said the rest is in the other car.
The boss wants to check the money.

185
00:20:11,760 --> 00:20:14,832
<i>If he agrees, we have no problem.</i>

186
00:20:14,920 --> 00:20:16,672
<i>Here, take the car keys.</i>

187
00:20:16,760 --> 00:20:19,718
<i>Go on. Take them.</i>

188
00:20:23,400 --> 00:20:25,152
<i>Come on. Come.</i>

189
00:20:26,680 --> 00:20:29,319
Okay, give me...
Give me some of the money.

190
00:20:36,200 --> 00:20:39,078
Give me some of the money!

191
00:20:40,960 --> 00:20:43,155
- Okay.
- You aren't going in there?

192
00:20:43,240 --> 00:20:47,233
- Yeah, I am, and so are you.
- Why am I going in there?

193
00:20:47,360 --> 00:20:51,194
- Why? To protect me.
- There is no protection there.

194
00:20:51,280 --> 00:20:54,636
If it's a come-on, we're fish in a barrel.
Why do they want you in there?

195
00:20:54,720 --> 00:20:57,029
- What are you, crazy?
- You know, you think too hard.

196
00:20:57,160 --> 00:21:00,630
Nobody ever told me that before.
But I wouldn't go in there.

197
00:21:02,280 --> 00:21:05,636
- What is it, Sam?
- I don't like it. Look at it.

198
00:21:07,240 --> 00:21:09,037
Okay, okay.

199
00:21:09,160 --> 00:21:11,469
Okay, let's just do it.
Let's just do it and be done, yeah?

200
00:21:12,400 --> 00:21:13,753
You don't wanna go in there.

201
00:21:15,240 --> 00:21:19,028
- I'm getting paid to go. It's that simple.
- Okay, come on. Let's go.

202
00:21:19,120 --> 00:21:22,590
If anything goes down,
get next to one of those guys.

203
00:21:22,680 --> 00:21:24,750
If there's a sniper,
he'll be afraid to shoot his own guy.

204
00:21:24,880 --> 00:21:26,472
- Let's go!
- All right.

205
00:21:47,720 --> 00:21:49,551
Stop!

206
00:21:49,640 --> 00:21:51,756
<i>Stay where you are.</i>

207
00:22:06,960 --> 00:22:09,474
<i>So, everything's fine.</i>

208
00:22:19,960 --> 00:22:21,916
Shit! I can't see! I can't see!

209
00:22:34,400 --> 00:22:36,231
Have some of this!

210
00:22:40,680 --> 00:22:42,193
Fuckin' arsehole!

211
00:22:46,600 --> 00:22:49,637
Fuckin' have some more, you bastards!

212
00:22:51,280 --> 00:22:53,111
Come on! Come on!

213
00:22:54,480 --> 00:22:56,789
Let's go!

214
00:22:56,920 --> 00:23:00,993
- No! You goddamn...
- Come on! Let's go!

215
00:23:13,480 --> 00:23:15,357
- Is anybody hurt?
- We're fine.

216
00:23:17,240 --> 00:23:21,836
Almost a bit of raspberry jam
back there, yeah?

217
00:23:21,920 --> 00:23:23,751
A bit of raspberry jam back there!

218
00:23:27,320 --> 00:23:30,869
Got the swag, kept the money.
Job well done.

219
00:23:30,960 --> 00:23:32,791
That's a fact. That is a fact.

220
00:23:57,240 --> 00:23:58,309
Slow down. Slow down.

221
00:24:00,320 --> 00:24:02,390
I think I have to stop.

222
00:24:30,120 --> 00:24:30,950
Thank you.

223
00:24:42,080 --> 00:24:43,877
Why did you take this job?

224
00:24:46,320 --> 00:24:48,276
My friend, I need the money.

225
00:24:49,360 --> 00:24:51,635
<i>The money is here.</i>

226
00:24:55,760 --> 00:24:58,797
That's what this is, you know? Money.

227
00:25:02,720 --> 00:25:04,551
Yeah, but who are our employers?

228
00:25:07,080 --> 00:25:08,877
You're right.

229
00:25:36,200 --> 00:25:37,997
Excuse me.

230
00:25:38,120 --> 00:25:40,554
Excuse me, monsieur.

231
00:25:49,000 --> 00:25:51,275
The Russians are bidding for the case.

232
00:25:51,360 --> 00:25:55,239
The case is in Nice.
They're trying to sell it to the Russians.

233
00:25:55,320 --> 00:25:58,471
They're staying at
the Villa Belle Mer in Nice.

234
00:25:59,560 --> 00:26:03,872
- The team isn't ready.
- Whatever the team is, you do it now.

235
00:26:03,960 --> 00:26:06,952
The Russians have decided to bid.
We need to move now.

236
00:26:07,080 --> 00:26:09,036
Excuse me.

237
00:26:09,240 --> 00:26:12,516
I have the information.
We'll be movin' very soon.

238
00:26:12,640 --> 00:26:14,471
It'll definitely
be in the nature of an ambush

239
00:26:14,600 --> 00:26:18,275
somewhere between here and here.

240
00:26:18,400 --> 00:26:22,632
We'll anticipate
a three-car convoy with a backup team.

241
00:26:22,720 --> 00:26:26,110
We will try and stop the target
before they can get away from us.

