00:57:20,000 --> 00:57:21,831
Sorry.

484
00:57:21,920 --> 00:57:23,876
- I'm sorry. I beg your pardon.
- It's all right.

485
00:57:23,960 --> 00:57:26,428
Uh, what do you need
a post office for?

486
00:57:26,520 --> 00:57:29,239
'Cause over here,
they use them for different things.

487
00:57:29,320 --> 00:57:30,196
I need your help.

488
00:57:31,800 --> 00:57:33,597
- I thought you left.
- I did leave.

489
00:57:33,720 --> 00:57:35,836
- You did leave? You're out?
- That's right.

490
00:57:35,920 --> 00:57:38,195
Can you help me? I need your help.

491
00:57:40,120 --> 00:57:41,917
What's the number?

492
00:57:46,120 --> 00:57:48,873
Yeah, the post office is, uh,
just down to your left.

493
00:57:49,000 --> 00:57:50,672
- Up on the left? Thanks.
- On the left.

494
00:57:58,320 --> 00:58:01,995
- A friend of yours?
- We went to high school together.

495
00:58:02,120 --> 00:58:05,271
Everyone's your brother
until the rent comes due.

496
00:58:05,360 --> 00:58:06,873
Ain't that the truth!

497
00:58:07,000 --> 00:58:09,355
<i>Yes. Yes, on the terrace?</i>

498
00:58:09,760 --> 00:58:11,159
<i>Facing me? I see him.</i>

499
00:58:11,240 --> 00:58:14,198
<i>Yes, I'll get him. Hang on, please.</i>

500
00:58:18,480 --> 00:58:19,913
<i>Excuse me, sir. Are you Sam?</i>

501
00:58:22,760 --> 00:58:23,590
Yeah.

502
00:58:23,680 --> 00:58:25,079
<i>Telephone for you.</i>

503
00:58:33,600 --> 00:58:35,431
Yeah, good to see you, too.

504
00:58:35,520 --> 00:58:38,273
If his position changes, I'll let you know.

505
00:58:44,680 --> 00:58:46,636
Gregor's in a town called Arles.

506
00:59:59,600 --> 01:00:01,909
He's at the arena.

507
01:00:33,000 --> 01:00:35,878
So this is the amphitheatre of Arles

508
01:00:36,000 --> 01:00:39,834
which was built
at the end of the first century AD.

509
01:00:39,960 --> 01:00:42,269
It is built with limestone.

510
01:00:49,440 --> 01:00:50,668
I know those men.

511
01:01:21,640 --> 01:01:24,552
And you can see
this dominant yellow colour

512
01:01:24,640 --> 01:01:27,074
which is actually caused
essentially by a lantern.

513
01:01:27,160 --> 01:01:29,799
We're not sure that the walls
were actually yellow.

514
01:01:29,880 --> 01:01:31,711
And so, now we will continue

515
01:01:31,840 --> 01:01:34,354
and visit the Roman baths
down this way.

516
01:01:47,440 --> 01:01:49,237
Yeah.

517
01:01:51,640 --> 01:01:55,394
Thank you, gentlemen.
That'll do nicely.

518
01:01:57,240 --> 01:01:59,037
It's Sergi. I remember you.

519
01:01:59,160 --> 01:02:01,799
Yes, Gregor, it's me.

520
01:02:01,880 --> 01:02:05,509
- How have you been?
- Well. These are trying times.

521
01:02:05,640 --> 01:02:08,598
- I'm sorry about the unfortunate incident.
- Oh, yeah.

522
01:02:08,760 --> 01:02:12,036
