572
01:09:10,240 --> 01:09:12,310
Keep it clean so I can see it.

573
01:09:16,560 --> 01:09:18,391
Yeah. That's it.

574
01:09:24,960 --> 01:09:26,996
All right.
What we're gonna do is routine.

575
01:09:27,120 --> 01:09:29,554
I've done this many times before.

576
01:09:29,680 --> 01:09:31,750
There are no vital organs, arteries.
It's okay.

577
01:09:31,880 --> 01:09:33,871
You won't kill me.
Just make sure you get the bullet

578
01:09:33,960 --> 01:09:35,951
- before you pry it out.
- All right.

579
01:09:36,080 --> 01:09:37,877
Take that scalpel.

580
01:09:42,200 --> 01:09:44,031
The upper part.

581
01:09:45,560 --> 01:09:47,471
Over here. Just cut up there.

582
01:09:47,560 --> 01:09:49,391
Just a little cut.

583
01:09:59,880 --> 01:10:01,677
Okay. Got it.

584
01:10:03,480 --> 01:10:05,277
Now take the clamp.

585
01:10:05,400 --> 01:10:07,994
Take the clamp and open up... the hole.

586
01:10:08,120 --> 01:10:10,588
Just put it in there.

587
01:10:11,640 --> 01:10:13,471
Put it in there.

588
01:10:13,560 --> 01:10:15,391
That's it. Put it in. Just...

589
01:10:15,520 --> 01:10:17,670
Now open it up. Spread it. Spread it.

590
01:10:17,760 --> 01:10:20,035
Okay. Okay.

591
01:10:20,120 --> 01:10:23,078
Now get the other...
Get the other clamps and get the bullet.

592
01:10:23,160 --> 01:10:25,116
Remember, don't take it out
unless you really got it.

593
01:10:42,800 --> 01:10:46,031
Do it again. Do it again.
Just try once more.

594
01:10:51,960 --> 01:10:55,430
I'm sorry.

595
01:10:57,280 --> 01:11:00,989
When he pulls it out, put the gauze in.
There's gonna be a lot of blood.

596
01:11:06,480 --> 01:11:08,277
Put the gauze there.

597
01:11:17,840 --> 01:11:20,115
Fucker sprayed his bullet with Teflon.

598
01:11:21,360 --> 01:11:25,069
He was trying to stamp me "paid in full".

599
01:11:25,240 --> 01:11:27,913
- Is that why it went through the vest?
- Yeah.

600
01:11:29,600 --> 01:11:32,239
You think you can stitch me up
on your own?

601
01:11:33,560 --> 01:11:37,030
If you don't mind,
I'm gonna pass out.

602
01:12:24,680 --> 01:12:27,035
You gonna kill me?

603
01:12:27,120 --> 01:12:30,874
No. I'm not gonna kill ya.

604
01:12:57,320 --> 01:12:59,117
Why would I want to kill ya?

605
01:13:17,560 --> 01:13:20,393
- I gave you a job.
- I did my job.

606
01:13:21,520 --> 01:13:23,112
So how'd it go wrong?

607
01:13:23,200 --> 01:13:25,156
I thought you wanted the case.

608
01:13:26,320 --> 01:13:28,038
Oh, we'll get the case.

609
01:13:28,120 --> 01:13:31,078
We'll get the case, eh, Gregor?

610
01:13:32,720 --> 01:13:34,551
Don't you worry about the case.

611
01:13:36,920 --> 01:13:38,956
What I want's an explanation.

612
01:13:39,080 --> 01:13:41,674
An explanation? For what?

613
01:13:41,840 --> 01:13:43,717
You bollixed it up.

614
01:13:43,880 --> 01:13:46,713
- I bollixed it up?
- You hired him.

615
01:13:46,800 --> 01:13:48,631
Through your fucking contact!

616
01:13:54,480 --> 01:13:57,995
- You didn't do your homework.
- Why did you have to kill Larry?

617
01:13:58,080 --> 01:13:59,911
Oh, Larry, is it?

618
01:14:01,000 --> 01:14:02,797
I was clearing up your mess.

619
01:14:02,880 --> 01:14:05,678
My mess?
Oh, well, you take over, then.

620
01:14:05,800 --> 01:14:07,597
- Eh?
- But you can't, can you?

621
01:14:07,720 --> 01:14:09,790
It's you that's hiding, isn't it, Seamus?

622
01:14:09,920 --> 01:14:12,195
It's you that can't show your face.

623
01:14:14,760 --> 01:14:18,070
Who else thinks that?
Who you been talking to?

624
01:14:18,200 --> 01:14:20,316
Isn't that the reason
why I'm doing this job?

625
01:14:23,800 --> 01:14:25,597
You're a good girl, Deirdre.

626
01:14:26,920 --> 01:14:28,751
Do your job, eh?

627
01:14:41,920 --> 01:14:43,956
<i>He's tough, your Yank.</i>

628
01:14:45,280 --> 01:14:46,838
<i>You're right about that.</i>

629
01:14:49,000 --> 01:14:50,194
<i>But who is he?</i>

630
01:14:51,840 --> 01:14:53,592
<i>That's not important.</i>

631
01:14:54,560 --> 01:14:57,199
<i>Didn't he work for the CIA?</i>

632
01:14:58,280 --> 01:14:59,998
<i>He used to.</i>

633
01:15:00,680 --> 01:15:02,113
<i>Not anymore?</i>

634
01:15:03,640 --> 01:15:05,232
<i>He's on the run.</i>

635
01:15:06,680 --> 01:15:08,113
<i>You're sure?</i>

636
01:15:08,200 --> 01:15:12,955
<i>I know what he can do.</i>
<i>I've seen him.</i>

637
01:15:13,040 --> 01:15:15,429
<i>Why would he carve himself up</i>
<i>if he were still CIA?</i>

638
01:15:15,520 --> 01:15:18,034
<i>He makes a call and it's taken care of.</i>

639
01:15:28,160 --> 01:15:30,071
<i>And you? How are you?</i>

640
01:15:38,480 --> 01:15:43,759
<i>We need some information.</i>
<i>We need to find some people in Paris.</i>

641
01:15:43,840 --> 01:15:44,795
<i>Who?</i>

642
01:15:45,280 --> 01:15:47,874
<i>An Irish man and woman,</i>

643
01:15:47,960 --> 01:15:50,110
<i>a German, an ex-KGB.</i>

644
01:15:50,880 --> 01:15:51,949
<i>They're professionals.</i>

645
01:15:52,040 --> 01:15:53,473
<i>They're in hiding.</i>

646
01:15:54,120 --> 01:15:57,078
<i>This is really important to you?</i>

647
01:15:59,200 --> 01:16:01,634
<i>He saved my life.</i>

648
01:16:04,400 --> 01:16:05,230
Bon.

649
01:16:07,560 --> 01:16:10,028
<i>I'll find them for you.</i>

650
01:16:28,000 --> 01:16:30,673
Where's the case?

651
01:16:34,040 --> 01:16:35,837
It will come tomorrow. I'm sure.

652
01:16:36,000 --> 01:16:39,390
Well, I'm sure it will, too. Let's go.

653
01:16:40,440 --> 01:16:42,670
Let's hope so, for your sake, anyway.

654
01:17:13,040 --> 01:17:15,110
Are you feeling better?

655
01:17:15,240 --> 01:17:17,356
Yeah, enough to move around. Thanks.

656
01:17:26,880 --> 01:17:28,677
My hobby.

657
01:17:29,760 --> 01:17:31,557
One grows old.

658
01:17:33,240 --> 01:17:35,037
I knew a lot of fellas, friends of mine,

659
01:17:35,160 --> 01:17:36,957
they just wanted to live to open a bar.

660
01:17:37,040 --> 01:17:39,395
Had they lived,
would they have done it?

661
01:17:42,440 --> 01:17:45,477
- Then they were spared their disillusion.
- Yeah, that's right.

662
01:17:47,440 --> 01:17:49,510
Who were these people?
Friends of yours?

663
01:17:52,240 --> 01:17:55,198
- I wouldn't hurt a friend.
- Was that my question?

664
01:17:56,640 --> 01:17:57,914
That's right.

665
01:18:03,200 --> 01:18:06,431
Well, who are you?

666
01:18:08,000 --> 01:18:11,356
A fella like you,
trying to make it to retirement.

667
01:18:11,480 --> 01:18:15,393
At the end of the day, we're likely
to be punished for our kindnesses.

668
01:18:15,480 --> 01:18:18,392
You don't have to worry about me.
I won't hurt you.

669
01:18:45,160 --> 01:18:47,355
The 47 ronin, do you know it?

670
01:18:49,280 --> 01:18:54,559
47 samurai whose master
was betrayed and killed by another lord.

671
01:18:54,640 --> 01:18:58,030
They became ronin, masterless samurai,

672
01:18:58,160 --> 01:19:00,276
disgraced by another man's treachery.

673
01:19:01,680 --> 01:19:04,148
For three years they plotted,
pretending to be thieves,

674
01:19:04,280 --> 01:19:06,874
mercenaries, even madmen.

675
01:19:07,000 --> 01:19:09,275
That I didn't have time to do.

676
01:19:09,360 --> 01:19:11,669
And then one night they struck,
slipping into the castle

677
01:19:11,800 --> 01:19:13,677
of their lord's betrayer, killing him.

678
01:19:15,080 --> 01:19:17,435
Nice. I like that. My kind of job.

679
01:19:17,560 --> 01:19:19,437
There's something more.

680
01:19:20,960 --> 01:19:24,919
All 47 of them committed seppuku,

681
01:19:25,040 --> 01:19:28,237
ritual suicide,
in the courtyard of the castle.

682
01:19:28,360 --> 01:19:31,033
Well, that I don't like so much.

683
01:19:31,160 --> 01:19:34,152
- But you understand it?
- What do you mean, I understand it?

684
01:19:36,120 --> 01:19:40,591
The warrior code, the delight in the battle.
You understand that, yes?

685
01:19:41,800 --> 01:19:44,598
But also something more.

686
01:19:44,680 --> 01:19:46,989
You understand there is something
outside yourself

687
01:19:47,080 --> 01:19:49,355
that has to be served.

688
01:19:49,480 --> 01:19:51,630
And when that need is gone,

689
01:19:51,760 --> 01:19:55,036
when belief has died, what are you?

690
01:19:55,120 --> 01:19:57,031
A man without a master.

691
01:19:57,200 --> 01:19:59,919
Right now I'm a man
without a pay cheque.

692
01:20:00,040 --> 01:20:03,635
The ronin could have hired
themselves to new masters.

693
01:20:03,720 --> 01:20:05,790
They could have fought
for themselves.

694
01:20:05,920 --> 01:20:08,798
But they chose honour.
They chose myth.

695
01:20:09,920 --> 01:20:11,672
They chose wrong.

696
01:20:19,160 --> 01:20:21,594
Seppu... Seppu... what?

697
01:20:21,720 --> 01:20:23,836
Yes, seppuku.

698
01:20:23,920 --> 01:20:26,070
Disembowelment.

699
01:20:26,200 --> 01:20:28,839
The sword goes in here.

700
01:20:38,520 --> 01:20:40,476
Are you sure this address is good?

701
01:20:40,600 --> 01:20:42,431
Jean-Pierre gave it to me.

702
01:21:14,520 --> 01:21:17,876
Under the bridge by the river...

703
01:21:17,960 --> 01:21:20,520
How did you know
it was an ambush?

704
01:21:20,640 --> 01:21:22,995
Whenever there is any doubt,
there is no doubt.

705
01:21:23,120 --> 01:21:24,917
That's the first thing they teach you.

706
01:21:28,520 --> 01:21:31,114
Who taught you?

707
01:21:31,240 --> 01:21:34,277
I don't remember.
That's the second thing they teach you.

708
01:21:39,240 --> 01:21:41,435
All good things
come to those who wait.

709
01:22:10,960 --> 01:22:14,430
- Why is Gregor still alive?
- He's taking them to the package.

710
01:22:38,000 --> 01:22:39,149
How ya doin'?

711
01:22:46,680 --> 01:22:49,319
What are you...
What are you gonna do to me?

712
01:22:49,440 --> 01:22:54,468
Let's just be calm for one more moment.
One more moment.

713
01:23:06,640 --> 01:23:08,631
Why? Why?

714
01:23:08,720 --> 01:23:10,711
You know why.

715
01:23:10,800 --> 01:23:12,870
No. You don't wanna do that.

716
01:23:16,520 --> 01:23:17,475
You can't.

717
01:23:22,200 --> 01:23:22,837
Get back!

718
01:23:24,360 --> 01:23:26,271
Get in the fucking car!

719
01:23:35,800 --> 01:23:37,313
Why didn't you shoot her?

720
01:24:27,360 --> 01:24:29,032
Take the tunnel, now!

721
01:24:29,120 --> 01:24:31,031
Oh, Christ!

722
01:24:33,240 --> 01:24:35,276
Eh, merde!

723
01:27:36,040 --> 01:27:37,359
Come on! Come on!

724
01:28:01,440 --> 01:28:03,317
All right, you fuck!

725
01:31:21,840 --> 01:31:24,115
Where could he be?

726
01:31:24,200 --> 01:31:27,988
- Where could he be?
- Hmm.

727
01:31:28,120 --> 01:31:31,430
The Irish and the Russians are looking
for him. So where does he go?

728
01:31:31,520 --> 01:31:35,229
He goes to the Russians
to make the deal for the case.

729
01:31:35,320 --> 01:31:38,676
Gregor ain't comin' in unless
he can figure out a safe exchange.

730
01:31:38,800 --> 01:31:40,870
He knows they'll kill him for the case
rather than pay him for it.

731
01:31:40,960 --> 01:31:46,114
He's got to work it out soon
before the Irish find him.

732
01:31:47,400 --> 01:31:49,152
So where does he go?

733
01:31:50,920 --> 01:31:52,717
You go to what you know.

734
01:31:56,120 --> 01:31:59,795
He's KGB.
He goes to one of his old safe houses.

735
01:32:01,200 --> 01:32:03,714
No, they're all blown.

736
01:32:03,840 --> 01:32:06,115
Where does he go?

737
01:32:11,640 --> 01:32:14,916
So, you're on the run.
Where do you go?

738
01:32:15,040 --> 01:32:16,871
Hmm?

739
01:32:20,840 --> 01:32:25,072
Where's he been? Where's he been?
Where's he been? Where's he been?

740
01:32:36,360 --> 01:32:38,828
He made the fake case.

741
01:32:38,920 --> 01:32:41,195
He had the fake case made.

742
01:32:41,320 --> 01:32:44,630
Gregor. He had it made.

743
01:32:44,720 --> 01:32:47,188
He had to have had it made.

744
01:32:48,640 --> 01:32:51,632
In Paris, before we went to Nice.

745
01:32:51,720 --> 01:32:53,472
He didn't have time to have it made.

746
01:32:53,560 --> 01:32:55,676
He bought something that looked like it,
then spray-painted it.

747
01:32:55,760 --> 01:32:58,228
Where did he get the spray?
He never left the room.

748
01:32:58,320 --> 01:33:00,231
Where did he get the case?

749
01:33:09,480 --> 01:33:11,630
Excusez-moi, monsieur.

750
01:33:32,080 --> 01:33:33,832
It's a case for ice skates.

751
01:33:37,280 --> 01:33:39,111
Why ice skates?

752
01:33:41,320 --> 01:33:43,231
And why would Gregor
know an ice-skate case?

753
01:33:45,160 --> 01:33:47,549
He didn't have time to have it made.

754
01:33:47,680 --> 01:33:52,276
He didn't have time to have it made.
The Russians made it.

755
01:33:54,160 --> 01:33:56,628
The Russians made it.

756
01:33:59,640 --> 01:34:01,437
We're following the wrong people.

757
01:34:01,560 --> 01:34:04,358
We don't have to find Gregor.

758
01:34:04,480 --> 01:34:07,074
We find the Russians,
they will take us to him.

759
01:34:07,200 --> 01:34:10,909
<i>You've lived in Paris</i>
<i>a long time. You know the people.</i>

760
01:34:11,000 --> 01:34:13,912
<i>- I get around.</i>
<i>- You meet the new Russians.</i>

761
01:34:14,000 --> 01:34:17,754
<i>You know how it is.</i>
<i>Ex-spies. Now it's Mafia.</i>

762
01:34:18,600 --> 01:34:20,636
<i>Under diplomatic cover.</i>

763
01:34:22,120 --> 01:34:23,075
<i>KGB?</i>

764
01:34:23,320 --> 01:34:24,275
<i>Ex-KGB.</i>

765
01:34:24,680 --> 01:34:29,071
<i>Heavy hitters, gamblers,</i>
<i>lots of money, big cars.</i>

766
01:34:29,160 --> 01:34:30,513
<i>They live like tsars.</i>
<i>Throw money away.</i>

767
01:34:30,600 --> 01:34:32,397
<i>Fur hats are expensive.</i>

768
01:34:32,480 --> 01:34:37,679
<i>- And bodyguards.</i>
<i>- Expensive coats, Dr Zhivago.</i>

769
01:34:37,760 --> 01:34:40,797
<i>I have a lot of work, no time.</i>

770
01:34:42,240 --> 01:34:43,798
<i>I understand.</i>

771
01:34:45,480 --> 01:34:47,118
<i>All right. Let's go.</i>

772
01:34:48,000 --> 01:34:48,955
Okay.

773
01:34:55,840 --> 01:34:57,353
<i>It will be fine.</i>

774
01:34:58,800 --> 01:35:00,597
The guy is gonna reach out.

775
01:35:00,680 --> 01:35:02,511
Is he any good?

776
01:35:02,640 --> 01:35:05,393
Jean-Pierre says if it's Russian
and it's in Paris...

777
01:35:16,040 --> 01:35:19,316
<i>If I wanted to find Russians</i>
<i>in Paris this week,</i>

778
01:35:19,400 --> 01:35:23,393
<i>I'd go to the ice show.</i>

779
01:36:34,400 --> 01:36:36,436
- Bonsoir, Pierre.
- Bonsoir.

780
01:36:36,520 --> 01:36:38,351
Je vais payer pour votre sour.

781
01:36:38,440 --> 01:36:41,671
Oh, merci beaucoup,
Mademoiselle Kirilova.

782
01:36:47,920 --> 01:36:52,471
<i>I'll trade you a cigarette for a favour.</i>

783
01:36:53,000 --> 01:36:54,831
<i>The favour is, steer clear of those guys.</i>

784
01:36:54,920 --> 01:36:56,353
<i>Who? The Russians?</i>

785
01:37:02,600 --> 01:37:04,716
<i>They sure throw their money around.</i>

786
01:37:05,800 --> 01:37:06,835
Bonsoir.

787
01:37:06,920 --> 01:37:09,036
- Ça va?
- Salut.

788
01:37:12,200 --> 01:37:13,997
- Bonsoir.
- Ah, bonsoir.

789
01:37:20,280 --> 01:37:24,432
The Russian is seeing Natacha Kirilova,
the star of the ice show.

790
01:37:24,520 --> 01:37:27,956
He spends every evening in the audience.

791
01:37:29,160 --> 01:37:30,593
How did you find that out?

792
01:37:30,680 --> 01:37:33,831
We went to high school together.

793
01:38:06,680 --> 01:38:09,035
<i>Mikhi, is everything all right?</i>

794
01:38:09,800 --> 01:38:11,153
<i>Everything is fine.</i>

795
01:38:12,320 --> 01:38:13,309
<i>Sweet girl.</i>

796
01:38:16,000 --> 01:38:16,955
<i>Go. Go on.</i>

797
01:38:35,160 --> 01:38:36,832
<i>Ladies and gentlemen!</i>

798
01:38:36,920 --> 01:38:40,071
<i>We are very proud to present...</i>

799
01:38:40,160 --> 01:38:46,759
<i>... two-time Olympic champion</i>
<i>and three-time World champion...</i>

800
01:38:46,840 --> 01:38:50,310
<i>... Natacha Kirilova!</i>

801
01:40:51,440 --> 01:40:53,271
Let's go.

802
01:41:06,080 --> 01:41:08,116
<i>Wait out here.</i>

803
01:41:12,880 --> 01:41:15,030
Yes, he is.

804
01:41:15,120 --> 01:41:17,111
Hello, Mikhi.

805
01:41:17,240 --> 01:41:21,074
- The meeting is not till later tonight.
- The meeting's now.

806
01:41:24,320 --> 01:41:25,833
You have the money?

807
01:41:27,120 --> 01:41:30,874
Well, we were going to go back
to get it before the meet.

808
01:41:30,960 --> 01:41:32,029
I don't think so.

809
01:41:33,440 --> 01:41:35,271
You have the money?

810
01:41:39,520 --> 01:41:42,398
I might have the money.
Where is the case?

811
01:41:42,480 --> 01:41:46,678
No, you have to do it.
I couldn't live with myself.

812
01:41:59,120 --> 01:42:00,917
I have the money.

813
01:42:01,040 --> 01:42:03,429
We conclude this now
and part friends.

814
01:42:03,520 --> 01:42:05,238
Okay?

815
01:42:08,000 --> 01:42:09,035
Where is the case?

816
01:42:20,920 --> 01:42:22,717
I'd like to be paid now.

817
01:42:28,080 --> 01:42:30,150
No doubt.

818
01:42:34,720 --> 01:42:36,517
Now tell me the other part.

819
01:42:37,920 --> 01:42:39,990
The other part?

820
01:42:40,120 --> 01:42:41,917
I'm leaving.

821
01:42:42,040 --> 01:42:44,793
I'm taking my fee and I'm leaving.

822
01:42:46,360 --> 01:42:49,318
I have a person with a rifle in the stadium.

823
01:42:49,520 --> 01:42:52,239
I've worked with her for years.
She never misses.

824
01:42:52,360 --> 01:42:55,193
I will call.

825
01:42:55,320 --> 01:42:57,550
I have to call within 45 seconds

826
01:42:57,680 --> 01:42:59,671
to say that I'm leaving,

827
01:42:59,800 --> 01:43:02,837
and then in another 10 minutes
to say that I'm safe.

828
01:43:04,440 --> 01:43:08,194
Should I be unable to call,
your friend will be shot.

829
01:43:17,640 --> 01:43:19,437
30 seconds, Mikhi.

830
01:43:20,800 --> 01:43:23,189
<i>- We need to get inside.</i>
<i>- You can't pass without badges.</i>

831
01:43:30,240 --> 01:43:31,992
20 seconds.

832
01:43:42,240 --> 01:43:43,195
10 seconds.

833
01:44:11,240 --> 01:44:13,993
<i>There were two of them.</i>

834
01:44:14,080 --> 01:44:15,718
<i>They were looking for those guys.</i>

835
01:44:15,800 --> 01:44:17,870
<i>Just a minute, sir!</i>

836
01:44:33,760 --> 01:44:37,514
<i>I am a Chilean citizen,</i>
<i>as you can see from my passport.</i>

837
01:44:37,600 --> 01:44:39,192
Merci.

838
01:45:16,080 --> 01:45:19,117
- Mama!
- Shh, shh, shh.

839
01:45:24,720 --> 01:45:26,278
Katchev!

840
01:45:26,360 --> 01:45:27,475
Qu'est-ce qui se passe?

841
01:45:41,880 --> 01:45:42,835
Stay with him.

842
01:46:14,360 --> 01:46:16,794
Get out of here.
Get out of here!

843
01:46:16,920 --> 01:46:19,639
Get out of the car.
Walk away. Walk away!

844
01:46:19,720 --> 01:46:22,439
Walk away! Go. Go.

845
01:46:22,520 --> 01:46:25,273
- I will if you will.
- Just go.

846
01:46:25,360 --> 01:46:27,715
Come with me.
Forget about the case.

847
01:46:31,960 --> 01:46:34,349
I didn't come for the case.
I came for your boss.

848
01:46:36,120 --> 01:46:38,588
I came for Seamus. I came for him.

849
01:46:39,920 --> 01:46:44,630
Just get out of here.
I never left. Don't you see?

850
01:46:45,960 --> 01:46:48,190
Get out of the way!
Get out of the way!

851
01:46:56,200 --> 01:46:57,474
Get out of the way!

852
01:46:57,560 --> 01:46:58,834
<i>This way is blocked.</i>

853
01:47:25,520 --> 01:47:27,317
I can take you in or leave you here.

854
01:47:28,760 --> 01:47:29,954
There. That's him with the case.

855
01:47:30,040 --> 01:47:32,076
<i>Sir! Over here, please.</i>

856
01:47:32,160 --> 01:47:32,876
<i>Wait! Wait!</i>

857
01:47:40,200 --> 01:47:43,112
<i>There are more back there!</i>

858
01:48:18,880 --> 01:48:20,677
Stay where you are!
Stay where you are!

859
01:48:20,760 --> 01:48:24,469
Don't move! Shut your fuckin' mouth up!
Shut your mouth!

860
01:48:37,920 --> 01:48:39,672
You stupid shite.

861
01:48:39,840 --> 01:48:43,230
You're a dead man.

862
01:49:04,840 --> 01:49:07,115
<i>This is the BBC World Service.</i>

863
01:49:07,240 --> 01:49:09,800
<i>It was announced today,</i>
<i>after almost 30 years</i>

864
01:49:09,920 --> 01:49:13,151
<i>of bloody and seemingly intractable</i>
<i>civil conflict in Northern Ireland,</i>

865
01:49:13,240 --> 01:49:15,071
<i>that a peace agreement</i>
<i>has been reached between</i>

866
01:49:15,200 --> 01:49:18,272
<i>the predominantly Protestant</i>
<i>government of that British-ruled enclave,</i>

867
01:49:18,400 --> 01:49:20,834
<i>and the Irish resistance...</i>

868
01:49:25,440 --> 01:49:28,876
<i>... have told CNN that it was</i>
<i>the apprehension and slaying</i>

869
01:49:29,000 --> 01:49:33,630
<i>in France of the Irish terrorist Seamus</i>
<i>O'Rourke, by parties still unknown,</i>

870
01:49:33,720 --> 01:49:35,950
<i>that contributed a stability,</i>
<i>largely allowing</i>

871
01:49:36,040 --> 01:49:39,874
<i>the negotiations to proceed</i>
<i>to their historic conclusion today.</i>

872
01:49:40,000 --> 01:49:42,798
<i>O'Rourke had earlier</i>
<i>been denounced by the IRA,</i>

873
01:49:42,920 --> 01:49:46,833
<i>the military wing of Sinn Fein,</i>
<i>as a rogue breakaway operative.</i>

874
01:49:49,240 --> 01:49:52,437
Well, then, good knowin' ya.

875
01:50:02,720 --> 01:50:03,675
Hmm?

876
01:50:03,760 --> 01:50:06,832
- I'm sorry?
- You said something.

877
01:50:06,920 --> 01:50:10,276
I said she would not
be coming back here.

878
01:50:12,360 --> 01:50:16,638
Yeah. She would
not be coming back here, would she?

879
01:50:22,640 --> 01:50:24,631
I can't even put my hand in my pocket
to pay the bill.

880
01:50:24,720 --> 01:50:26,790
I'll get it.

881
01:50:29,200 --> 01:50:30,952
I'll get the next one.

882
01:50:37,040 --> 01:50:38,712
What was in the case?

883
01:50:38,920 --> 01:50:40,876
I don't remember.

884
01:50:42,160 --> 01:50:43,639
Lesson number two.

885
01:50:45,720 --> 01:50:47,517
Keep in touch.

886
01:51:05,280 --> 01:51:07,032
Let's go.

887
01:51:19,720 --> 01:51:22,393
No questions, no answers.

888
01:51:22,480 --> 01:51:24,516
That's the business we're in.

889
01:51:24,600 --> 01:51:26,795
You accept it and move on.

890
01:51:28,160 --> 01:51:30,833
Maybe that's lesson number three.

